            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThe%20stump%20in%20this%20dream%20typified%20King%20Nebuchadnezzar.%20His%20pride%20had%20brought%20him%20to%20the%20point%20of%20his%20becoming%20obnoxious%20to%20God.%20Indeed%2C%20he%20ruled%20the%20entire%20known%20world%20and%20lived%20in%20the%20most%20magnificent%20city%20in%20the%20world.%20His%20construction%20of%20the%20hanging%20gardens%20of%20Babylon%20is%20still%20considered%20one%20of%20the%20eight%20wonders%20of%20the%20world.%20However%2C%20the%20time%20came%20when%20God%20had%20to%20humble%20him.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ENebuchadnezzar%20may%20have%20been%20king%2C%20but%20God%20is%20%22Chairman%22%20of%20the%20%22Ways%20and%20Means%20Committee%22!%20He%20is%20in%20charge%2C%20and%20%22he%20is%20able%20to%20humble%20those%20who%20are%20proud%22%20(Daniel%204%3A37).%20God%20removed%20Nebuchadnezzar's%20intellect%20and%20made%20him%20eat%20grass%20like%20a%20cow%20for%20seven%20years.%20In%20His%20mercy%2C%20however%2C%20He%20did%20not%20totally%20destroy%20him%2C%20but%20left%20him%20as%20a%20stump%2C%20restoring%20everything%20to%20him%20the%20moment%20the%20trial%20was%20over.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EYou%20may%20feel%20like%20you%20have%20lost%20everything%2C%20but%20in%20fact%2C%20your%20stump%20is%20still%20intact.%20God%20may%20have%20disciplined%20you%2C%20but%20He%20still%20loves%20you.%20And%20when%20God%20restores%20you%2C%20it%20will%20be%20with%20%22even%20greater%20honor%20than%20before%22%20(v.%2036).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ECheer%20up%2C%20all%20you%20%22stumps.%22%20The%20best%20is%20yet%20to%20be!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
